Show data shape¶

In [3]:
print(f"The data has {df.shape[0]} Rows, and {df.shape[1]} Columns")

The data has 56 Rows, and 8 Columns

Compare the each airline by Available seat kilometers flown every week¶

In [4]:
# Create the figure 
plt.figure(figsize=(15,6))

# Get the values 
x = df.iloc[:,:2]
x = x.sort_values(by=["avail_seat_km_per_week"], ascending=False)
x1 = x.iloc[:,0]
x2 = x.iloc[:,1]

# Plot the values
plt.scatter(x=x1, y=x2, color='skyblue', label='avail_seat_km_per_week')
# Rotate the xticks
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
# Title for the plot
plt.title('Compare the each airline by Available seat kilometers flown every week', size=15)

# Show the legend and plot 
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Show Top 10
x.iloc[:10,:].reset_index(drop=True)
